#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an4.85"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.85:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.85:0.2"
msgid "9. Macalavagga "
msgstr "9. Confirmed "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: tamotamaparāyanasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an4.85:0.3"
msgid "85. Tamotamasutta "
msgstr "85. From Darkness to Darkness "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an4.85:1.1"
msgid "“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, these four people are found in the world. "

msgctxt "an4.85:1.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

#. VAR: tamaparāyaṇo → … parāyano (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
#. HTML: </p><ol>
msgctxt "an4.85:1.3"
msgid "Tamo tamaparāyaṇo, tamo jotiparāyaṇo, joti tamaparāyaṇo, joti jotiparāyaṇo. "
msgstr "~The dark bound for darkness, ~the dark bound for light, ~the light bound for darkness, and ~the light bound for light. "

#. HTML: </ol><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an4.85:2.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo tamo hoti tamaparāyaṇo? "
msgstr "And how is a person dark and bound for darkness? "

msgctxt "an4.85:2.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo nīce kule paccājāto hoti—caṇḍālakule vā venakule vā nesādakule vā rathakārakule vā pukkusakule vā dalidde appannapānabhojane kasiravuttike, yattha kasirena ghāsacchādo labbhati. "
msgstr "It’s when someone is reborn in a low family—a family of outcastes, bamboo-workers, hunters, chariot-makers, or waste-collectors—poor, with little to eat or drink, where life is tough, and food and shelter are hard to find. "

msgctxt "an4.85:2.3"
msgid "So ca hoti dubbaṇṇo duddasiko okoṭimako bavhābādho kāṇo vā kuṇī vā khañjo vā pakkhahato vā, na lābhī annassa pānassa vatthassa yānassa mālāgandhavilepanassa seyyāvasathapadīpeyyassa. "
msgstr "And they’re ugly, unsightly, deformed, chronically ill—one-eyed, crippled, lame, or half-paralyzed. They don’t get to have food, drink, clothes, and vehicles; garlands, fragrance, and makeup; or bed, house, and lighting. "

msgctxt "an4.85:2.4"
msgid "So kāyena duccaritaṃ carati, vācāya duccaritaṃ carati, manasā duccaritaṃ carati. "
msgstr "And they do bad things by way of body, speech, and mind. "

msgctxt "an4.85:2.5"
msgid "So kāyena duccaritaṃ caritvā, vācāya duccaritaṃ caritvā, manasā duccaritaṃ caritvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati. "
msgstr "When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell. "

msgctxt "an4.85:2.6"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo tamo hoti tamaparāyaṇo. "
msgstr "That’s how a person is dark and bound for darkness. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an4.85:3.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo tamo hoti jotiparāyaṇo? "
msgstr "And how is a person dark and bound for light? "

msgctxt "an4.85:3.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo nīce kule paccājāto hoti—caṇḍālakule vā venakule vā nesādakule vā rathakārakule vā pukkusakule vā dalidde appannapānabhojane kasiravuttike, yattha kasirena ghāsacchādo labbhati; "
msgstr "It’s when some person is reborn in a low family … "

msgctxt "an4.85:3.3"
msgid "so ca hoti dubbaṇṇo duddasiko okoṭimako bavhābādho kāṇo vā kuṇī vā khañjo vā pakkhahato vā na lābhī annassa pānassa vatthassa yānassa mālāgandhavilepanassa seyyāvasathapadīpeyyassa. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.85:3.4"
msgid "So kāyena sucaritaṃ carati, vācāya sucaritaṃ carati, manasā sucaritaṃ carati. "
msgstr "But they do good things by way of body, speech, and mind. "

msgctxt "an4.85:3.5"
msgid "So kāyena sucaritaṃ caritvā, vācāya sucaritaṃ caritvā, manasā sucaritaṃ caritvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati. "
msgstr "When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm. "

msgctxt "an4.85:3.6"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo tamo hoti jotiparāyaṇo. "
msgstr "That’s how a person is dark and bound for light. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.86, sc4
msgctxt "an4.85:4.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo joti hoti tamaparāyaṇo? "
msgstr "And how is a person light and bound for darkness? "

msgctxt "an4.85:4.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo ucce kule paccājāto hoti—khattiyamahāsālakule vā brāhmaṇamahāsālakule vā gahapatimahāsālakule vā aḍḍhe mahaddhane mahābhoge pahūtajātarūparajate pahūtavittūpakaraṇe pahūtadhanadhaññe; "
msgstr "It’s when some person is reborn in an eminent family—a well-to-do family of aristocrats, brahmins, or householders—rich, affluent, and wealthy, with lots of gold and silver, lots of property and assets, and lots of money and grain. "

msgctxt "an4.85:4.3"
msgid "so ca hoti abhirūpo dassanīyo pāsādiko paramāya vaṇṇapokkharatāya samannāgato, lābhī annassa pānassa vatthassa yānassa mālāgandhavilepanassa seyyāvasathapadīpeyyassa. "
msgstr "And they’re attractive, good-looking, lovely, of surpassing beauty. They get to have food, drink, clothes, and vehicles; garlands, fragrance, and makeup; and bed, house, and lighting. "

msgctxt "an4.85:4.4"
msgid "So kāyena duccaritaṃ carati, vācāya duccaritaṃ carati, manasā duccaritaṃ carati. "
msgstr "But they do bad things by way of body, speech, and mind. "

msgctxt "an4.85:4.5"
msgid "So kāyena duccaritaṃ caritvā, vācāya duccaritaṃ caritvā, manasā duccaritaṃ caritvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati. "
msgstr "When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell. "

msgctxt "an4.85:4.6"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo joti hoti tamaparāyaṇo. "
msgstr "That’s how a person is light and bound for darkness. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an4.85:5.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo joti hoti jotiparāyaṇo? "
msgstr "And how is a person light and bound for light? "

msgctxt "an4.85:5.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo ucce kule paccājāto hoti—khattiyamahāsālakule vā brāhmaṇamahāsālakule vā gahapatimahāsālakule vā aḍḍhe mahaddhane mahābhoge pahūtajātarūparajate pahūtavittūpakaraṇe pahūtadhanadhaññe; "
msgstr "It’s when some person is reborn in an eminent family … "

msgctxt "an4.85:5.3"
msgid "so ca hoti abhirūpo dassanīyo pāsādiko paramāya vaṇṇapokkharatāya samannāgato, lābhī annassa pānassa vatthassa yānassa mālāgandhavilepanassa seyyāvasathapadīpeyyassa. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.85:5.4"
msgid "So kāyena sucaritaṃ carati, vācāya sucaritaṃ carati, manasā sucaritaṃ carati. "
msgstr "And they do good things by way of body, speech, and mind. "

msgctxt "an4.85:5.5"
msgid "So kāyena sucaritaṃ caritvā, vācāya sucaritaṃ caritvā, manasā sucaritaṃ caritvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati. "
msgstr "When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm. "

msgctxt "an4.85:5.6"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo joti hoti jotiparāyaṇo. "
msgstr "That’s how a person is light and bound for light. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.85:5.7"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti. "
msgstr "These are the four people found in the world.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.85:5.8"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

